media.headline: Finnegan records first strikeout
media.blurb: PHI@CIN: Finnegan records first K of the season
media.bigblurb: Brandon Finnegan strikes out Aaron Altherr looking for his first strikeout of the season in the top of the 2nd inning

media.headline: Eickhoff's first K of the season
media.blurb: PHI@CIN: Eickhoff records his first K of the year
media.bigblurb: Jerad Eickhoff records his first strikeout of the season by getting Adam Duvall to swing and miss in the bottom of the 2nd inning

media.headline: Votto's solo home run
media.blurb: PHI@CIN: Votto hits a solo homer to break the tie
media.bigblurb: Joey Votto hits a solo home run to right field to give the Reds a 1-0 lead in the bottom of the 7th inning

media.headline: Cozart's RBI single adds to lead
media.blurb: PHI@CIN: Cozart hits RBI single to add to Reds' lead
media.bigblurb: Zack Cozart hits an RBI single through the right side to bring home Adam Duvall and give the Reds a 2-0 lead

media.headline: Franco's diving stop
media.blurb: PHI@CIN: Franco makes diving stop to stop Reds' rally
media.bigblurb: Maikel Franco makes a diving stop at third and throws across to first base to retire Tucker Barnhart and keep the deficit at 2

media.headline: Votto recovers for nice putout
media.blurb: PHI@CIN: Votto combines with Finnegan for the putout
media.bigblurb: Joey Votto recovers after bobbling the hard-hit ground ball and throws to Brandon Finnegan covering at first base for the third out

media.headline: Herrera steals second
media.blurb: CIN@PHI: Herrera steals second on overturned call
media.bigblurb: Odubel Herrera steals second base following an overturned call in the 9th inning

media.headline: Iglesias notches the save
media.blurb: PHI@CIN: Iglesias fans Joseph to earn the save
media.bigblurb: Raisel Iglesias strikes out Tommy Joseph to earn the save and the Reds' 2-0 win over the Phillies

media.headline: Finnegan strikes out nine
media.blurb: PHI@CIN: Finnegan fans nine over seven shutout frames
media.bigblurb: Brandon Finnegan strikes out nine batters over seven shutout innings, allowing one hit and one walk to earn the win in the Reds' 2-0 victory

media.headline: Finnegan on dominant victory
media.blurb: PHI@CIN: Finnegan reacts to terrific start
media.bigblurb: Reds starter Brandon Finnegan discusses his outstanding season debut in which he held the Phillies to just one hit over seven scoreless

media.headline: Eickhoff strikes out six batters
media.blurb: PHI@CIN: Eickhoff fans six over 6 2/3 innings of work
media.bigblurb: Jerad Eickhoff strikes out six Reds batters over 6 2/3 innings of work, allowing two runs on five hits and a walk vs. the Reds

media.headline: Recap: PHI 0, CIN 2
media.blurb: 4/5/17: Finnegan's seven scoreless innings paces Reds
media.bigblurb: Daily Recap: Brandon Finnegan tossed seven innings of one-hit ball with nine strikeouts and Joey Votto hit a solo homer in the Reds' 2-0 win

media.headline: Price on Finnegan's gem
media.blurb: PHI@CIN: Price discusses Finnegan's stellar start
media.bigblurb: Reds manager Bryan Price breaks down the pitching performance of Brandon Finnegan in the win over the Phillies
